Package com.vernalis.pdbconnector2.graphql.result

This package contains classes and annotations to define and parse the results of a GraphQL query

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    GraphQLResult
    This interface marks the implementing class as the result of a GraphQL.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    GraphQLResultIterator
    An Iterator which wraps a GraphQLResult iterator, along with the remaining query path
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    GraphQLResultException
    This Exception represents some sort of error whilst trying to retrieve a result from a GraphQLResult
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    GraphQLAlias
    This annotation is processed by GraphQLResult to return fields with a name different to their query path
    GraphQLFlatten
    This annotation is used to indicate that an intermediate result of iterable queries should have any iterable results added directly to the parent rather than as nested lists.
    GraphQLIterate
    This annotation indicates to the result parser that the returned intermediate query (which will be an Iterable<? extends GraphQLResult>) should be iterated to find all subqueries
    GraphQLRoot
    This annotation serves to indicate that the annotated type is a root level of a query result, e.g.
